23/06/2008
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Dubrovnik police on Sunday (June 22nd) announced the arrest of two people suspected of drug trafficking. 
Police seized 5kg of cocaine worth 550,000 euros in a joint operation involving officers from Zagreb, Dubrovnik and Split. 
Officials say the drugs entered the country in a bag carried into the country by a female Paraguayan citizen, who delivered it to a Croat national. 
(HRT, RIA Novosti - 22/06/08)
